Title   : PepsiCo Global CEO Ramon Laguarta meets PM Modi
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-17T15:56:31
Fetched : 2025-09-18T06:31:51.666474
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/pepsico-global-ceo-ramon-laguarta-meets-pm-modi/article70062451.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PepsiCo Global CEO and Chairman Ramon Laguarta, who is on an India visit, met with the Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Tuesday, the company stated in a Linkedin post. This is the second visit of the global chief of the snacks and beverges major in this year to India after April.
“Yesterday, our Chairman & CEO Ramon Laguarta was honored to meet with the Prime Minister in New Delhi to discuss strengthening PepsiCo’s long-term commitment to India and exploring opportunities for collaboration in areas such as manufacturing, sustainability, innovation, and community development,” the company stated in a social media post on Wednesday.
Laguarta is in India with the members of the company’s global excutive committee.
“The discussion reinforced our long-term commitment to India as a key growth market. PepsiCo has been part of India’s growth story for more than three decades, and we remain committed to investing in its future while making a positive impact for communities, consumers, and the economy,” the company added.
PepsiCo has identified India as one of its key strategic growth market for the next few years. The company has been ramping up its manufacturing footprint in the country in the past few years.
Most recently, it has been allotted land in Sipcot Industrial Park, at Mannaparrai in Tamil Nadu, where it will be setting up a snacks plant.. It is in the process of opening up a new greenfield in Assam.
It has made significant investments in its greenfield facility for snacks in Uttar Pradesh, while it is also setting up a flavour manufacturing facility in Madhya Pradesh.
PepsiCo India reported a consolidated net profit of ₹883.39 crore in CY 2024, while consolidated revenue from operations stood at ₹9,096.62 crore.
Published on September 17, 2025

