Title   : EaseMyTrip Partners with Hoi to launch smart rewards program at Indian airports 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-18T06:29:41
Fetched : 2025-09-18T06:36:58.261928
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/logistics/easemytrip-partners-with-hoi-to-launch-smart-rewards-program-at-indian-airports/article70064533.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Travel platform EaseMyTrip has partnered with airport tech company Hoi to introduce India’s first Smart Kiosk Rewards Program across three major airports. The three-month initiative targets passengers at Delhi’s Indira Gandhi International Airport, Hyderabad’s Rajiv Gandhi International Airport, and Goa’s Manohar International Airport.
Under the program, passengers ordering food through Hoi’s contactless kiosks receive instant ₹500 EaseMyTrip coupons via WhatsApp. A monthly draw awards one traveler a ₹5,000 voucher. The initiative has already served over 5,000 passengers since launch.
The partnership leverages Hoi’s existing contactless food-ordering infrastructure to eliminate traditional airport queues while providing travel rewards. Passengers can bypass conventional dining lines and earn benefits for future bookings simultaneously.
“This collaboration represents our vision of airports as dynamic ecosystems rather than mere transit points,” said Dhruv Godara, Deputy CEO of Hoi. The company operates across Delhi, Hyderabad, and Goa airports, offering integrated services including flight tracking, baggage updates, and concierge services.
EaseMyTrip CEO Rikant Pittie emphasized the program transforms routine airport dining into value creation opportunities. The listed travel-tech platform, operational since 2008, offers zero-convenience fees and access to over 400 airlines and 2.9 million hotels globally.
The partnership represents a shift in airport monetization, moving beyond transactional relationships toward integrated travel ecosystems that connect dining, technology, and future travel planning.
.
Published on September 18, 2025

