Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-18

Title   : Ganesh Consumer Products sets IPO price band at ₹306-322 per share, offer to open on September 22
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-17T15:14:17
Fetched : 2025-09-18T07:03:44.405464
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/ganesh-consumer-products-sets-ipo-price-band-at-306-322-per-share-offer-to-open-on-september-22/article70062323.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FMCG maker Ganesh Consumer Products has fixed the price band of ₹306-322 per equity share of face value ₹10 each for its initial public offer (IPO), which is scheduled to open on September 22.
The IPO of the Kolkata-based company consists of a fresh issue worth ₹130 crore and an offer for sale of 86.58 lakh equity shares. At the upper-end of the price brand, the company aims to raise around ₹409 crore.
The offer will close on September 24. Investors can bid for a minimum of 46 equity shares and in multiples of 46 equity shares thereafter.
The proceeds from the fresh issue to the extent of ₹60 crore would be utilised for prepayment or repayment of all or a portion of certain outstanding borrowings availed by the company; ₹45 crore would be utilised for funding capital expenditure for setting up a roasted gram flour and gram flour manufacturing unit in Darjeeling, West Bengal; and the rest for general corporate purposes.
Market share
In terms of value sold in the last financial year, the company is the third-largest brand of packaged whole wheat flour (atta) and largest brand in wheat-based derivatives (maida, sooji, dalia) in East India. In this region, in terms of value for FY25, the company is also one of the top two players for packaged sattu and besan.
The company’s products are sold under its flagship brand Ganesh. Its revenue from operations stood at ₹850.46 crore in FY25, while net profit was ₹35.4 crore during the period.
DAM Capital Advisors, IIFL Capital Services, and Motilal Oswal Investment Advisors are the book-running lead managers.
Published on September 17, 2025

Title   : PNB, Tata Consumer among 6 stocks that rose above VWAP 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-18T03:41:51
Fetched : 2025-09-18T07:03:44.405464
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/pnb-tata-consumer-among-6-stocks-that-rose-above-vwap/slideshow/123962730.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
On September 17, the closing prices of six stocks in the Nifty500 pack rallied over 0.5% relative to their VWAP (Volume Weighted Average Price), and a shift above the VWAP suggests a potential bullish trend, according to stockedge.com's technical scan data.
When the closing price rises above the VWAP, it signifies that the closing price is higher than the average price at which it was traded throughout the day, with the average being weighted by trading volume. This occurrence is often interpreted as a potential bullish signal by traders and investors. Potentially indicating positive sentiment in the market.

